## NCP Rewrite

eXMC automatically applies Non-Centered Parameterization (NCP) to hierarchical
models. This improves sampling efficiency by reparameterizing
`alpha ~ Normal(mu, sigma)` as `alpha_raw ~ Normal(0, 1)` with
`alpha = mu + sigma * alpha_raw`.

```elixir
{trace, stats} =
  Sampler.sample(ir, %{"mu_group" => 4.0, "sigma_group" => 1.0, "alpha" => 4.0},
    num_samples: 500,
    seed: 42,
    num_warmup: 300
  )

IO.inspect(Map.keys(trace), label: "Variables sampled")
```

<!-- livebook:{"output":true} -->

```
Variables sampled: ["alpha", "mu_group", "sigma_group"]
```

<!-- livebook:{"output":true} -->

```
["alpha", "mu_group", "sigma_group"]
```

## Posterior Summary

```elixir
summary = Exmc.Diagnostics.summary(trace)

for {name, s} <- Enum.sort(summary) do
  IO.puts("#{name}: mean=#{Float.round(s.mean, 3)} std=#{Float.round(s.std, 3)}")
end
```

<!-- livebook:{"output":true} -->

```
alpha: mean=4.094 std=0.212
mu_group: mean=-0.91 std=7.569
sigma_group: mean=6.25 std=3.53
```

