## Multi-Chain Sampling

Run multiple chains for convergence diagnostics:

```elixir
{traces, stats_list} =
  Sampler.sample_chains(ir, 4,
    init_values: %{"mu_group" => 4.0, "sigma_group" => 1.0, "alpha" => 4.0},
    num_samples: 300,
    seed: 42,
    num_warmup: 200
  )

IO.puts("Chains: #{length(traces)}")
```

<!-- livebook:{"output":true} -->

```
Chains: 4
```

<!-- livebook:{"output":true} -->

```
:ok
```

## R-hat Convergence Diagnostic

R-hat measures between-chain vs within-chain variance. Values near 1.0 indicate convergence.

```elixir
for name <- Map.keys(hd(traces)) |> Enum.sort() do
  chains_for_var = Enum.map(traces, fn t -> t[name] end)
  rhat = Exmc.Diagnostics.rhat(chains_for_var)
  IO.puts("#{name}: R-hat = #{Float.round(rhat, 3)}")
end
```

<!-- livebook:{"output":true} -->

```
alpha: R-hat = 1.0
mu_group: R-hat = 1.02
sigma_group: R-hat = 1.001
```

<!-- livebook:{"output":true} -->

```
[:ok, :ok, :ok]
```

## Multi-Chain Trace Overlay

```elixir
alias VegaLite, as: Vl

for name <- ["mu_group", "alpha", "sigma_group"] do
  chain_data =
    traces
    |> Enum.with_index()
    |> Enum.flat_map(fn {t, chain_idx} ->
      t[name]
      |> Nx.to_flat_list()
      |> Enum.filter(&is_number/1)
      |> Enum.with_index(fn val, i ->
        %{"iteration" => i, "value" => val, "chain" => "chain #{chain_idx}"}
      end)
    end)

  Vl.new(width: 600, height: 200, title: "#{name} — 4 chains")
  |> Vl.data_from_values(chain_data)
  |> Vl.mark(:line, opacity: 0.6)
  |> Vl.encode_field(:x, "iteration", type: :quantitative)
  |> Vl.encode_field(:y, "value", type: :quantitative)
  |> Vl.encode_field(:color, "chain", type: :nominal)
  |> Kino.render()
end
```

